title: BBQ Bourbon Bacon Burger
description: Layer on the flavor with this booze-infused burger. Beef patties are seasoned with Whiskey Dust rub and sprinkled with brown sugar, hot sauce, and bourbon before hitting the fridge to marinate. Finished by smoking on the Traeger with Whiskey Blend pellets and topped with crispy bacon and melty cheddar cheese.

steps.step: In a medium bowl, combine ground beef and Whiskey Dust rub and mix well using caution not to overwork or allow the beef to get too warm.
Divide the ground beef into 6 portions and form into patties using 6-inch cake rings or by hand. Press down and form the beef into uniform patties.

With a skewer, poke about 40 holes about ¾ inch deep through each patty. Spread brown sugar all over the top of the patties, then drizzle with hot sauce. Pour bourbon over each burger, transfer to the fridge and let marinate for about 30 minutes.
When ready to cook, set grill temperature to 225°F and preheat with lid closed for 10-15 minutes.
Remove burgers from the fridge. When the grill reaches temperature, place bacon and burgers directly on the grill grate. Turn on Super Smoke if available.
Cook until burgers reach an internal temperature of 165°F. In the last 10 minutes of cooking, top each burger with a slice of cheddar cheese to melt. Total cook time is typically 45-60 minutes.
Remove burgers and bacon from the grill. Let rest for 2-3 minutes, then build your burgers with your favorite toppings and enjoy!

author: Traeger Kitchen
